&lt;p align=&quot;center&quot;>&#xD;
    &lt;strong>Query Source BD Technical Roles Model&lt;/strong>&#xD;
&lt;/p></problem>
  <goals>&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Customer Researcher Role&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The adhoc subprocess Query Source Info&amp;nbsp;allows the Customer Researcher&amp;nbsp;to query Reports and Source&#xD;
    Information, get the results and review the returned information. They may do additional queries for&amp;nbsp;until&#xD;
    completed.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h5>&#xD;
    Activities&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/h5>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Uses the Query Reports, query Source&amp;nbsp;and Review Reports, Review Source&amp;nbsp;activities.&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Research Writer Role&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The adhoc subprocess Query Source Info&amp;nbsp;allows the Research Writer&amp;nbsp;to query Source Information, get the&#xD;
    results and review the returned information. They may do additional queries for&amp;nbsp;Source Information until&#xD;
    completed. Research Writers produce Research Reports that address information needs of customers based upon completed&#xD;
    research. The Report Writers reviews the research information provided by Research Analysts and determines if: enough&#xD;
    information is there to produce a report, insufficient information&amp;nbsp;was provided, or the report task is not&#xD;
    required (for various reasons). If&amp;nbsp; there is insufficient information available at this time, addition research&#xD;
    may be done.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h5>&#xD;
    Activities&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/h5>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Uses the Query Reports and Review Reports&amp;nbsp;activities.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&lt;br />&#xD;
&lt;h3>&#xD;
    Research Analyst Role&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/h3>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    The adhoc subprocess Query Source and Query Reports allows the Research Analyst to query Source Information and&#xD;
    Research Reports, get the results and review the returned information. They may do additional queries&#xD;
    for&amp;nbsp;information until completed. Research Analysts do the research prior to a report being written. If the&#xD;
    analysis of the source information results in the discovery of information that addresses a Customer Information Need a&#xD;
    new Report Task&amp;nbsp;is created&amp;nbsp;that forms the basis for the report. A draft report may be written as well.&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p>&#xD;
&lt;h5>&#xD;
    Activities&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/h5>&#xD;
&lt;p>&#xD;
    Uses the Query Reports, query Source&amp;nbsp;and Review Reports, Review Source&amp;nbsp;activities.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&#xD;
&lt;/p></goals>
